            "Type": "Input",
            "ValueType": "Simple Object",
            "IsArray": false,
            "Description": "Object identifying an EXISTING record to update, e.g. { \"ID\": \"...\" }. Most MJ entities use a single ID field; composite keys are supported via multiple key/value pairs. Accepts a JSON string as well. Omit this to create a new record (requires CreateIfMissing=true).",
            "IsRequired": false
